Gombe renown philanthropist and politician Jamil Isiyaku Gwamna (Sardaunan Gombe), has commiserated with the family of late Dr. Isa Muhammad Wade who died today after a brief illness. Gwamna described the Associate Professor’s death as a colossal, great, and irreparable loss. In a statement posted on his Facebook page, Jamil Gwamna stated that the death of the Dr. Wade will definitely create a vacuum not only for his immediate family, people of the state but to the nation in general. According to the statement, “I woke up this morning and received sad news of the death of an illustrious son of Gombe state and a distinguished academic, Dr. Isa Muhammad Wade. <img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-211823" src="https://i1.wp.com/leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Jamilu-Gwamna.jpg?resize=498%2C600&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="498" height="600" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Jamilu-Gwamna.jpg?resize=498%2C600&amp;ssl=1 498w, https://i1.wp.com/leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Jamilu-Gwamna.jpg?resize=768%2C924&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i1.wp.com/leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Jamilu-Gwamna.jpg?w=1080&amp;ssl=1 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 498px) 100vw, 498px" data-recalc-dims="1" />  “I sincerely extend my heartfelt condolence to his family, the people of Yamaltu Deba, and Gombe state as a whole. “My thoughts and prayers are with you in this period of pains. I pray to Allah to forgive his shortcomings and grant him eternal rest.” The statement read.